To create a floating label for your input fields in a web application, you can use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript or a CSS framework like Bootstrap or Material-UI  [1]. Here's a simple implementation using HTML and CSS:

HTML:
```html
<div class="floating-label">
  <input type="text" id="input-text" class="floating-input" placeholder=" " required>
  <label for="input-text" class="floating-label">Your Label</label>
</div>
```

CSS:
```css
.floating-label {
  position: relative;
}

.floating-input,
.floating-label {
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 24px;
}

.floating-input {
  display: block;
  padding: 8px 0;
  border: none;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;
  outline: none;
  transition: border-color 0.3s ease;
}

.floating-label {
  position: absolute;
  top: 16px;
  left: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
  color: #9b9b9b;
  transition: 0.3s ease top, 0.3s ease color;
}

.floating-input:focus,
.floating-input:not(:placeholder-shown) {
  border-color: #000;
}

.floating-input:focus + .floating-label,
.floating-input:not(:placeholder-shown) + .floating-label {
  top: -8px;
  color: #000;
}
```

This code creates a floating label effect by positioning the label absolutely within a relative container [2]. When the input field is focused or has content, the label moves to the top and changes color [3]. The transition property provides a smooth animation effect as the label transitions to the focused state [4].

